               <item n="project_comment_old">&lt;p&gt;Alternative classifications:
&lt;table class="table_lines"&gt;
  &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td title="MP"&gt;Peyrot&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td title="A2"&gt;archaic II&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td title="MM"&gt;Malzahn&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;–&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td title="TT"&gt;Tamai&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td title="C1"&gt;II-1 (600-700)&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td title="TTC14"&gt;Tamai-C14&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;–&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Translations from [[Peyrot, ToSu]]
&lt;table class="table_lines"&gt;
&lt;th&gt;Lines&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;th&gt;Translation&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;th&gt;Pages&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;a1-4&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;If a being here puts a &lt;i&gt;tanamoda &lt;/i&gt;seed into its mouth and swallows it as a whole without having chewed, then it does not notice the taste. Likewise, if someone who has learned the law does not sit down in meditation, the teaching is for him like a &lt;i&gt;tanamoda &lt;/i&gt;seed swallowed as a whole.&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;315&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;a5-b2&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;If this earth were without island and full of water all over, and there were a turtle without eyes that lived there for a long time, and there were also a yoke in this water with only one hole, light and not steady, and in a hundred years this turtle lifted its head and pulled it in quickly only once, and then its head would be pulled up in that hole – …&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;329&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Translations from [[Schmidt KT 1974]]
&lt;table class="table_lines"&gt;
&lt;th&gt;Lines&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;th&gt;Translation&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;th&gt;Pages&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;a1-2&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;span title="If (a being here) puts a corn soaked in (corn) liquor into [his] mouth [and] swallows it unchewed [and] whole, [then] he does not recognise its taste."&gt;Wenn (hier ein Wesen) ein mit (Korn)schnaps getränktes(?) Korn in den Mund nimmt [wtl. sich in den Mund legt] [und] es unzerkaut ganz hinunterschluckt, [so] erkennt er dessen Geschmack nicht.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;178, 354&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;a5-b3&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;span title="[Suppose that] this earth was without islands [and] full of water everywhere, [that] there were an eye-less turtle ..., and [that] there was a yoke in this water with [only] one opening ..., [that] every hundred years only, the turtle lifted [her] head and retracted [it] immediately again [and that] her head raised itself [lit. pulled itself up] into [this] opening [OR: was pulled up into this opening]: more difficult [even] than this [it is] for beings to be [re]born among the humans again from the state of animals."&gt;[Gesetzt], es wäre insellos diese Erde [und] allerorten voll von Wasser, es wäre eine augenlose Schildkröte ..., und es wäre ein Joch in diesem Wasser mit [nur] einer Öffnung ..., alle hundert Jahre nur erhöbe die Schildkröte den Kopf und zöge [ihn] gleich wieder ein [und] ihr Kopf erhöbe sich [wtl. zöge sich hoch] in die[se] Öffnung [bzw. würde in die[se] Öffnung hochgezogen]: Schwerer [noch] als dies [ist es] für die Lebewesen, aus dem Tierstande unter Menschen [wieder]geboren zu werden.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;300-1, 302-3&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;</item>
